data.meta_description: Serving around 2.5 million passengers per year, Leipzig Halle Airport (LEJ) is a busy, dual-terminal facility providing an essential gateway into and out of the Federal State of Saxony in Germany. Flights from the airport serve domestic cities such as Frankfurt, Munich, Dortmund and Dusseldorf, and EU destinations such as Mallorca, Paris and Fuerteventura.
